<div class="thumbinner" style="width:202px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Circumzenithalarc.jpg" class="image" title="The Circumzenithal Arc over Grand Forks, ND"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/Circumzenithalarc.jpg/200px-Circumzenithalarc.jpg" width="200" height="267" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Circumzenithalarc.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
The Circumzenithal Arc over <a href="/wiki/Grand_Forks,_ND" title="Grand Forks, ND" class="mw-redirect">Grand Forks, ND</a></div>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Afterglow" title="Afterglow">Afterglow</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Airglow" title="Airglow">Airglow</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Alexander%27s_band" title="Alexander's band">Alexander's band</a>, the dark region between the two bows of a double rainbow.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Alpenglow" title="Alpenglow">Alpenglow</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Anticrepuscular_rays" title="Anticrepuscular rays">Anticrepuscular rays</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Auroral_light" title="Auroral light" class="mw-redirect">Auroral light</a> (northern and southern lights, aurora borealis and aurora australis)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Belt_of_Venus" title="Belt of Venus">Belt of Venus</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Circumzenithal_arc" title="Circumzenithal arc">Circumzenithal arc</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Crepuscular_rays" title="Crepuscular rays">Crepuscular rays</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Earthquake_light" title="Earthquake light">Earthquake lights</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Lightning#Elves" title="Lightning">Elves</a> <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2003/01/21/science/21SHUT.html?todaysheadlines" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2003/01/21/science/21SHUT.html?todaysheadlines" rel="nofollow">[1]</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Glory_(optical_phenomenon)" title="Glory (optical phenomenon)">Glories</a> (also known as <i>Brocken's Specter</i> or <i>Specter of the Brocken</i>)</li>
