<li><a href="/wiki/Halo_(optical_phenomenon)" title="Halo (optical phenomenon)">Halos</a>, of Sun or Moon, including <a href="/wiki/Sun_dog" title="Sun dog">sun dogs</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Heiligenschein" title="Heiligenschein">Heiligenschein</a> or halo effect, partly caused by the <a href="/wiki/Opposition_effect" title="Opposition effect">Opposition effect</a></li>
<li><a href="/w/index.php?title=Iridescent_Clouds&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Iridescent Clouds (page does not exist)">Iridescent Clouds</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Light_pillar" title="Light pillar">Light pillar</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Rainbow" title="Rainbow">Rainbows</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Mirage" title="Mirage">Mirages</a> (including <a href="/wiki/Fata_Morgana_(mirage)" title="Fata Morgana (mirage)">Fata Morgana</a>)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Sprite_(lightning)" title="Sprite (lightning)">Sprites</a> <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2003/01/21/science/21SHUT.html?todaysheadlines" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2003/01/21/science/21SHUT.html?todaysheadlines" rel="nofollow">[2]</a></li>
</ul>
